Privacy Policy for WiFi Analyzer PI
Last updated: January 1, 2025

This Privacy Policy explains how WiFi Analyzer PI ("we", "us", or "our") handles user information. By using the app, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.

1. Data Collection & Usage
- WiFi Analyzer PI does not collect, store, or share any personal data.
- The app only reads network-related data from the Android system API and displays it to the user in real-time.
- Information accessed includes network strength, latency, security type, network standard, router gateway, local device IP, subnet mask, DHCP lease, and other network-related details.
- No data is sent to external servers, third parties, or stored locally.

2. Permissions Required
WiFi Analyzer PI requires the following permissions to function properly:
- Location Permission (ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION, ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION) – Required by Android to access Wi-Fi network information.
- Network & Wi-Fi Permissions (ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE, ACCESS_WIFI_STATE, CHANGE_NETWORK_STATE, CHANGE_WIFI_STATE) – Used to display Wi-Fi and network details.
- Hardware Permission (android.hardware.location.gps) – Necessary for scanning nearby networks.

The app does not track, store, or transmit user location.

3. Third-Party Services & Advertising
- WiFi Analyzer PI does not use third-party SDKs, analytics, or external APIs.
- The app does not display ads or serve any personalized content.
- No data is shared with advertisers or third-party services.

4. Security & Compliance
- Since no user data is collected or stored, no additional security measures are required.
- The app complies with Google Play's Data Safety requirements.
- WiFi Analyzer PI does not target or collect data from children under 13.

5. Updates & Contact
This Privacy Policy may be updated if necessary. Any changes will be posted on the app’s store page and website.

For any questions or concerns, contact us at:
ilirhdev@gmail.com

Summary: WiFi Analyzer PI does not collect, store, or share any user data. It only displays network information that is available on the device through system APIs. No ads, no tracking, and no third-party involvement.